1
00:00:00,770 --> 00:00:01,770
What?

2
00:00:01,770 --> 00:00:02,770
(Episode 130)

3
00:00:02,770 --> 00:00:03,880
Real father?

4
00:00:04,580 --> 00:00:06,210
Lee Kang Hyuk, you...

5
00:00:06,210 --> 00:00:07,480
Lee Kang Hyuk is Jun Ho's...

6
00:00:09,250 --> 00:00:10,480
He's your father?

7
00:00:28,830 --> 00:00:32,940
Is it true? Lee Kang Hyuk,
are you Jun Ho's biological father?

8
00:00:33,340 --> 00:00:36,270
Nam Bong, don't listen to Manager Lee.

9
00:00:36,270 --> 00:00:38,580
You saw how Jun Ho just stormed out.
Do you still not believe me?

10
00:00:38,940 --> 00:00:40,250
Should I say it again?

11
00:00:40,310 --> 00:00:41,310
I'm...

12
00:00:43,080 --> 00:00:45,880
I'm Jun Ho's biological father.

13
00:00:48,690 --> 00:00:51,090
Nam Bong, pay him no mind.

14
00:00:51,390 --> 00:00:53,660
Manager Lee is just spouting nonsense.

15
00:00:58,360 --> 00:00:59,430
Hwa Young.

16
00:01:00,030 --> 00:01:02,300
I'm not backing down anymore.

17
00:01:02,700 --> 00:01:05,370
You and Jun Ho are both mine.

18
00:01:06,500 --> 00:01:07,710
I'm not leaving this house.

19
00:01:09,410 --> 00:01:11,580
Kang Nam Bong,
you're the one who's leaving.

20
00:01:15,480 --> 00:01:17,050
That bastard...

21
00:01:18,650 --> 00:01:20,520
- Wait, Nam Bong...
- Hey, you bastard.

22
00:01:26,120 --> 00:01:28,660
You bastard. So what if you're
Jun Ho's biological father?

23
00:01:28,730 --> 00:01:30,330
Why are you bothering Hwa Young?

24
00:01:30,430 --> 00:01:33,430
You're the one who came between me
and Hwa Young. You pathetic jerk.

25
00:01:33,430 --> 00:01:35,070
Please, both of you, just stop it.

26
00:01:38,040 --> 00:01:40,470
(Trustworthy Police, Safe Nation)

27
00:01:56,820 --> 00:01:59,090
I've brought proof
of Oh Jang Mi's innocence.

28
00:01:59,460 --> 00:02:01,630
How did you find it so quickly...

29
00:02:02,890 --> 00:02:05,660
This is the report on the bloodstains
at Chairman Ma's crime scene.

30
00:02:06,000 --> 00:02:07,570
Oh Jang Mi's departure time
was captured...

31
00:02:07,570 --> 00:02:09,570
in the Dream Hotel's
underground parking garage.

32
00:02:09,930 --> 00:02:12,200
Her arrival time was recorded
by the security CCTV...

33
00:02:12,200 --> 00:02:13,670
at the Chairman's front gate.

34
00:02:14,070 --> 00:02:18,140
While the times from the hotel
and the Chairman's gate line up,

35
00:02:18,440 --> 00:02:21,050
the living room CCTV
isn't a security model,

36
00:02:21,050 --> 00:02:23,550
- so the timestamp can be manipulated.
- That is...

37
00:02:23,550 --> 00:02:26,720
If you check, you'll see that the time
Oh Jang Mi entered the house...

38
00:02:26,950 --> 00:02:30,190
and the time the officers arrived
are exactly six minutes apart.

39
00:02:30,520 --> 00:02:32,190
However, as you can see in the report,

40
00:02:32,490 --> 00:02:35,830
it states that the blood had been
coagulating for at least 30 minutes.

41
00:02:36,560 --> 00:02:38,500
How do you explain this time discrepancy?

42
00:02:39,030 --> 00:02:40,100
It's impossible, isn't it?

43
00:02:40,330 --> 00:02:43,130
But the responding officers
said they heard them fighting.

44
00:02:43,900 --> 00:02:45,240
Are you sure that's what they heard?

45
00:02:45,440 --> 00:02:47,110
That they were fighting
over a deed of transfer?

46
00:02:47,210 --> 00:02:49,440
They said they heard fighting
and things breaking.

47
00:02:49,510 --> 00:02:52,580
That could have been a Bluetooth speaker
or a doctored recording.

48
00:02:53,550 --> 00:02:54,810
And while we're at it,

49
00:02:55,410 --> 00:02:57,450
you got the fingerprint analysis
for the deed of transfer back, right?

50
00:02:57,780 --> 00:03:00,050
I heard that Oh Jang Mi's prints
weren't on it,

51
00:03:01,120 --> 00:03:02,290
and you're aware of that,
aren't you, Detective?

52
00:03:02,920 --> 00:03:03,960
Well...

53
00:03:04,820 --> 00:03:08,060
And this is the access path
used to alter the CCTV footage.

54
00:03:08,590 --> 00:03:09,960
It includes the server logs.

55
00:03:10,230 --> 00:03:13,870
If you check to see whose phone
is registered to that server address,

56
00:03:14,130 --> 00:03:16,400
you'll find your real suspect.

57
00:03:17,000 --> 00:03:20,510
All right. I'll review this
and get back to you.

58
00:03:20,670 --> 00:03:23,780
Please hold off on the warrant request
and review this as quickly as possible.

59
00:03:29,950 --> 00:03:30,950
Hwa Young.

60
00:03:31,380 --> 00:03:34,690
- I'm heading to my lecture.
- Okay. See you later.

61
00:03:46,970 --> 00:03:48,630
- Unbelievable...
- Kang Hyuk.

62
00:03:49,470 --> 00:03:50,500
Here, have some coffee.

63
00:04:02,380 --> 00:04:03,410
Did you sleep well?

64
00:04:05,750 --> 00:04:07,490
Kang Hyuk, don't be like that.

65
00:04:08,550 --> 00:04:10,920
You're the only one
I can trust and rely on.

66
00:04:11,560 --> 00:04:14,530
Nam Bong is just temporary.

67
00:04:16,430 --> 00:04:18,760
Do you think I'm some invisible man
with no self-respect?

68
00:04:19,060 --> 00:04:20,800
I know. You have every right to be angry.

69
00:04:21,670 --> 00:04:24,170
But you're my flesh and blood.

70
00:04:24,670 --> 00:04:25,940
I truly mean that.

71
00:04:27,240 --> 00:04:30,610
And besides, you're the father of my son.

72
00:04:31,440 --> 00:04:32,780
You're Jun Ho's Dad.

73
00:04:35,550 --> 00:04:36,610
So you're acknowledging me...

74
00:04:37,520 --> 00:04:39,380
as Jun Ho's Dad?

75
00:04:39,520 --> 00:04:40,690
Of course.

76
00:04:40,990 --> 00:04:42,420
Blood ties can't be changed.

77
00:04:44,490 --> 00:04:45,490
Hwa Young.

78
00:04:46,590 --> 00:04:48,660
Regardless of what
I may have said over the years,

79
00:04:49,490 --> 00:04:53,870
why do you think I've kept you
by my side for so long?

80
00:04:54,830 --> 00:04:57,570
It's because you're the father of my son.

81
00:04:59,370 --> 00:05:00,470
Then why...

82
00:05:01,970 --> 00:05:04,210
Why won't you accept me as your man?

83
00:05:04,410 --> 00:05:06,740
I told you. You're like family to me.

84
00:05:07,250 --> 00:05:08,850
Nam Bong makes my heart race.

85
00:05:09,950 --> 00:05:13,380
Please try to understand
and just bear with me on that.

86
00:05:15,620 --> 00:05:17,160
So Kang Nam Bong is a man to you,

87
00:05:19,790 --> 00:05:21,890
but I'm like family to you, is that it?

88
00:05:22,190 --> 00:05:23,260
I'm sorry.

89
00:05:25,030 --> 00:05:26,030
Fine.

90
00:05:28,400 --> 00:05:31,870
I'll stay by your side as Jun Ho's Dad,
just like I am now.

91
00:05:32,570 --> 00:05:34,110
And I won't cause any more trouble.

92
00:05:35,370 --> 00:05:36,470
Okay. Thank you.

93
00:05:38,780 --> 00:05:39,880
Do you want more coffee?

94
00:05:41,250 --> 00:05:42,250
Quiet.

95
00:05:43,210 --> 00:05:44,680
It's the detective we bribed.

96
00:05:47,350 --> 00:05:48,350
Yes, Detective.

97
00:05:49,320 --> 00:05:50,320
What did you say?

98
00:05:51,090 --> 00:05:54,990
You're saying Lawyer Kang Baek Ho
presented that evidence?

99
00:05:57,060 --> 00:06:00,300
- I'm home, Mom.
- Baek Ho. You must be tired.

100
00:06:01,430 --> 00:06:04,170
Oh my goodness, look at all this sweat.

101
00:06:05,270 --> 00:06:07,240
I found all the evidence
to prove Jang Mi's innocence...

102
00:06:07,240 --> 00:06:08,640
and turned it over to the police.

103
00:06:09,210 --> 00:06:13,910
Right. We had to if we want her released
before they file for an arrest warrant.

104
00:06:14,050 --> 00:06:15,610
And just as we predicted,

105
00:06:15,650 --> 00:06:18,020
I found evidence
that Chae Hwa Young framed her.

106
00:06:18,120 --> 00:06:21,150
Then Jang Mi should be released soon.

107
00:06:21,320 --> 00:06:23,390
Her mother will be so happy.

108
00:06:25,620 --> 00:06:27,790
Hello, Detective.
About the evidence review...

109
00:06:29,090 --> 00:06:31,660
What did you say?
What do you mean the evidence isn't valid?

110
00:06:32,600 --> 00:06:33,770
That's ridiculous.

111
00:06:34,600 --> 00:06:36,970
I'm glad I was able to get in touch
with Detective Lee so quickly.

112
00:06:37,340 --> 00:06:40,540
Then, he'll file for an arrest warrant
for Oh Jang Mi right away, won't he?

113
00:06:40,710 --> 00:06:43,240
I heard Lawyer Kang went back
to the police station to protest,

114
00:06:43,670 --> 00:06:44,980
but it probably won't do him any good.

115
00:06:45,580 --> 00:06:47,710
Oh, and by the way,
it looks like Lawyer Kang...

116
00:06:47,980 --> 00:06:49,650
went into Chairman Ma's study yesterday.

117
00:06:49,850 --> 00:06:50,920
He did?

118
00:06:51,780 --> 00:06:53,420
Then he must have seen the documents.

119
00:06:53,890 --> 00:06:55,890
Did you leave the safe open on purpose?

120
00:06:56,090 --> 00:06:57,160
Of course.

121
00:06:57,720 --> 00:07:01,260
He needs to learn that
Chairman Ma killed his grandfather.

122
00:07:01,360 --> 00:07:02,930
That's how
we'll get to Kang Baek Ho, right?

123
00:07:03,590 --> 00:07:06,600
That way, when it's time to make a deal,
we'll have the upper hand.

124
00:07:20,650 --> 00:07:22,110
Looks like your mother came to visit.

125
00:07:22,980 --> 00:07:26,020
Seeing you in more comfortable clothes
makes me feel a little better.

126
00:07:26,350 --> 00:07:29,250
As soon as they started allowing visitors,

127
00:07:29,550 --> 00:07:31,660
my mom brought me clothes and underwear.

128
00:07:33,720 --> 00:07:36,390
The clothes smell
like our family's laundry detergent,

129
00:07:36,790 --> 00:07:38,600
so it almost feels like I'm at home.

130
00:07:38,800 --> 00:07:40,830
It's helped me relax a little.

131
00:07:41,530 --> 00:07:43,630
I brought you a cardigan and some socks.

132
00:07:44,070 --> 00:07:46,870
And I brought some snacks.
They'll be delivered to you later.

133
00:07:46,940 --> 00:07:48,040
Baek Ho.

134
00:07:48,670 --> 00:07:49,970
I'm okay.

135
00:07:50,810 --> 00:07:53,810
So please, don't push yourself too hard.

136
00:07:54,180 --> 00:07:55,180
Jang Mi.

137
00:07:56,680 --> 00:07:57,880
By the end of today, I'll...

138
00:08:01,790 --> 00:08:02,790
No.

139
00:08:04,160 --> 00:08:06,760
At the latest,
before they file for an arrest warrant,

140
00:08:07,160 --> 00:08:09,560
I'll find a way to get you out,
so don't you worry.

141
00:08:09,660 --> 00:08:10,900
I suspect...

142
00:08:11,660 --> 00:08:13,460
Chae Hwa Young has probably
gotten to the detectives...

143
00:08:13,530 --> 00:08:14,770
and the Prosecutor's Office already.

144
00:08:15,130 --> 00:08:17,030
- It won't be easy.
- No.

145
00:08:18,240 --> 00:08:19,670
There has to be a way.

146
00:08:20,810 --> 00:08:21,970
Wait...

147
00:08:21,970 --> 00:08:24,210
You're not planning on
breaking me out of here, are you?

148
00:08:30,180 --> 00:08:31,180
Baek Ho.

149
00:08:31,780 --> 00:08:33,720
I trust you.

150
00:08:34,320 --> 00:08:37,320
But please,
don't take any unnecessary risks.

151
00:08:37,720 --> 00:08:39,090
If you get hurt,

152
00:08:40,060 --> 00:08:41,290
it'll be harder on me.

153
00:08:41,990 --> 00:08:44,260
- Okay?
- Don't worry, Jang Mi.

154
00:08:45,100 --> 00:08:46,730
I promise I'll come get you,

155
00:08:47,400 --> 00:08:48,400
so just wait a little longer.

156
00:08:51,470 --> 00:08:52,670
I love you, Jang Mi.

157
00:09:28,240 --> 00:09:30,010
You're here sooner than I expected,
Kang Baek Ho.

158
00:09:30,340 --> 00:09:32,180
Let's cut to the chase.

159
00:09:33,180 --> 00:09:35,110
Get Jang Mi released now.

160
00:09:35,250 --> 00:09:37,480
Me? And why would I do that?

161
00:09:37,550 --> 00:09:40,750
The evidence I submitted
all pointed to you as the culprit,

162
00:09:41,620 --> 00:09:42,820
so you must've been pretty scared, right?

163
00:09:43,190 --> 00:09:45,260
Evidence? What evidence?

164
00:09:45,260 --> 00:09:46,560
If you don't get her out right now,

165
00:09:46,960 --> 00:09:49,830
I'll just have to leak all the evidence
I've been collecting.

166
00:09:50,290 --> 00:09:51,300
Let's go down together.

167
00:09:52,000 --> 00:09:54,200
Then we'll see who has more to lose.

168
00:09:54,330 --> 00:09:55,830
Are you threatening me?

169
00:09:55,930 --> 00:09:58,000
Would you like me to threaten you
as Kang Baek Ho the lawyer?

170
00:09:58,100 --> 00:10:01,910
Or as Choi Ha Joon,
the majority shareholder of Dream Group?

171
00:10:02,670 --> 00:10:05,010
- What are you talking about?
- You don't have a choice.

172
00:10:06,280 --> 00:10:08,710
I'm not here to negotiate.
I'm here to give you my terms.

173
00:10:09,650 --> 00:10:10,650
First.

174
00:10:11,420 --> 00:10:13,880
If an arrest warrant is issued
for Jang Mi,

175
00:10:14,350 --> 00:10:17,120
I'll leak to the press that
you kidnapped Ma Seo Rin as a baby...

176
00:10:17,590 --> 00:10:19,920
and that you forged a DNA test
to deceive the Chairman...

177
00:10:19,920 --> 00:10:21,060
about his daughter.

178
00:10:21,130 --> 00:10:22,190
Hey, Kang Baek Ho.

179
00:10:23,090 --> 00:10:25,000
You know what kind of person
Chairman Ma is.

180
00:10:25,260 --> 00:10:27,030
He's the man who killed your grandfather.

181
00:10:27,800 --> 00:10:29,530
And you're trying to help
the granddaughter of a man like that?

182
00:10:30,740 --> 00:10:34,170
Your grandfather, who died saving you,
must be turning in his grave.

183
00:10:34,310 --> 00:10:35,310
Second.

184
00:10:35,940 --> 00:10:37,810
I'll return as Choi Ha Joon,
the majority shareholder,

185
00:10:38,180 --> 00:10:41,180
and vote against
every resolution you propose.

186
00:10:41,650 --> 00:10:45,580
In other words,
you'll never get to be Chairman or CEO.

187
00:10:45,750 --> 00:10:47,350
You must underestimate Dream Group.

188
00:10:47,890 --> 00:10:49,720
Do you think
you're the only shareholder here?

189
00:10:49,850 --> 00:10:52,520
Then you leave me no choice.
I'll have to leak it to the press.

190
00:10:53,520 --> 00:10:54,860
The media is the fastest way
to get things done.

191
00:10:57,700 --> 00:10:58,700
Yes, Reporter Jeong.

192
00:10:59,100 --> 00:11:01,600
- I'm about to give an exclusive scoop.
- Kang Baek Ho.

193
00:11:01,930 --> 00:11:02,930
What do you think you're doing?

194
00:11:03,200 --> 00:11:06,240
All right, fine.
I'll do what you want, okay?

195
00:11:07,910 --> 00:11:09,470
I'll call you back.

196
00:11:12,780 --> 00:11:13,780
Kang Baek Ho.

197
00:11:14,650 --> 00:11:15,880
You've certainly grown a backbone.

198
00:11:16,210 --> 00:11:18,080
First, get Jang Mi released.

199
00:11:18,450 --> 00:11:20,250
Then we can talk about
negotiating or threats.

200
00:11:20,650 --> 00:11:21,850
I have nothing to lose.

201
00:11:25,120 --> 00:11:27,320
(Hanguk National University Hospital)

202
00:11:31,430 --> 00:11:33,230
You're here.

203
00:11:34,370 --> 00:11:37,670
You must be so busy
acting as Jang Mi's lawyer.

204
00:11:37,800 --> 00:11:39,270
How is the Chairman doing?

205
00:11:40,570 --> 00:11:42,040
Still the same.

206
00:11:42,040 --> 00:11:43,810
I guess
he doesn't feel like waking up yet.

207
00:11:44,340 --> 00:11:45,910
Stay strong.

208
00:11:46,980 --> 00:11:50,050
I was just at the courthouse
filing for a restraining order...

209
00:11:50,150 --> 00:11:52,620
and an application
for temporary guardianship.

210
00:11:53,080 --> 00:11:56,250
Does that mean Chae Hwa Young
can't come here?

211
00:11:56,420 --> 00:11:58,660
We should get an emergency ruling
this afternoon at the earliest...

212
00:11:58,790 --> 00:12:01,990
or by tomorrow morning at the latest.

213
00:12:02,830 --> 00:12:04,500
From that point on, if Chae Hwa Young...

214
00:12:04,830 --> 00:12:07,260
comes within a hundred meters
of the hospital,

215
00:12:07,330 --> 00:12:09,630
we can call the police
and have her arrested for trespassing.

216
00:12:10,330 --> 00:12:13,300
How can I ever thank you?

217
00:12:13,540 --> 00:12:16,870
Please don't say that.
We’re about to be in-laws, after all.

218
00:12:17,070 --> 00:12:20,010
And we're practically family already.

219
00:12:22,750 --> 00:12:24,950
Fine. I'll get Oh Jang Mi off the hook.

220
00:12:25,250 --> 00:12:27,890
In exchange, you drop this nonsense
about kidnapping...

221
00:12:28,150 --> 00:12:29,920
and the DNA forgery.

222
00:12:29,920 --> 00:12:31,960
You keep making me repeat myself.

223
00:12:32,760 --> 00:12:34,430
I'm the one holding all the cards.

224
00:12:34,760 --> 00:12:36,690
You don't have a choice.

225
00:12:37,260 --> 00:12:39,230
Even without your help,
I can prove Jang Mi's innocence.

226
00:12:39,230 --> 00:12:40,560
It'll just take more time.

227
00:12:40,800 --> 00:12:43,130
- Then go right ahead.
- However,

228
00:12:43,470 --> 00:12:45,600
I'll make sure you go down
as the real culprit.

229
00:12:45,870 --> 00:12:47,640
You'll be at a bigger disadvantage
if this gets out to the media.

230
00:12:48,070 --> 00:12:49,070
You want to know why?

231
00:12:49,370 --> 00:12:51,410
Because when the real culprit is revealed,
the spotlight will be...

232
00:12:52,010 --> 00:12:54,010
on the fact that Chae Hwa Young,
the current CEO of Dream Hotel,

233
00:12:54,350 --> 00:12:56,050
has become a criminal.

234
00:12:56,380 --> 00:12:58,520
What do you mean
I become the real culprit?

235
00:12:59,450 --> 00:13:02,190
- I never attacked Chairman Ma.
- Is that so?

236
00:13:02,990 --> 00:13:04,220
So you want to do this the hard way?

237
00:13:05,120 --> 00:13:06,120
Choi Ha Joon.

238
00:13:07,420 --> 00:13:09,490
You're betraying your grandfather.

239
00:13:09,830 --> 00:13:12,760
There's a transfer agreement
he signed with his blood and tears.

240
00:13:12,760 --> 00:13:13,960
You haven't seen it, have you?

241
00:13:14,030 --> 00:13:15,030
You're lying.

242
00:13:15,530 --> 00:13:17,130
My grandfather and the Chairman
were friends.

243
00:13:17,200 --> 00:13:19,340
Do friends exchange official seals
with each other?

244
00:13:20,240 --> 00:13:22,910
Chairman Ma didn't make you
a major shareholder out of atonement.

245
00:13:23,340 --> 00:13:27,280
It was just bait to shut you up
in case you found out the truth.

246
00:13:27,880 --> 00:13:30,110
Your grandfather died saving you,

247
00:13:30,410 --> 00:13:32,620
but Chairman Ma has been living
in luxury because of it.

248
00:13:36,020 --> 00:13:37,020
He took the bait.

249
00:13:38,220 --> 00:13:39,720
I'll let Oh Jang Mi go.

250
00:13:40,360 --> 00:13:42,230
But if even one line
of what I just told you...

251
00:13:42,590 --> 00:13:44,800
gets out to the press,

252
00:13:44,800 --> 00:13:46,000
I will immediately...

253
00:13:46,260 --> 00:13:49,500
destroy the original deed
to your grandfather's land.

254
00:13:49,900 --> 00:13:51,870
And I'm the only one
who knows where it is.

255
00:13:51,870 --> 00:13:55,370
So you won't be able to prove
Chairman Ma is guilty.

256
00:13:55,570 --> 00:13:58,310
I'll find out for myself
if the Chairman is my sworn enemy or not.

257
00:13:58,780 --> 00:14:01,580
And right now, the most important thing
is Jang Mi's release.

258
00:14:01,780 --> 00:14:02,810
So don't change the subject.

259
00:14:02,810 --> 00:14:05,020
So you'll agree to my condition, right?

260
00:14:08,320 --> 00:14:10,220
The moment I confirm Jang Mi is released,

261
00:14:10,790 --> 00:14:12,120
I'll drop the complaint.

262
00:14:13,160 --> 00:14:15,960
But the moment you betray me
or lay a hand on Jang Mi,

263
00:14:16,290 --> 00:14:17,330
the deal is off.

264
00:14:17,390 --> 00:14:19,630
To think you'd postpone
your own grandfather's revenge...

265
00:14:19,630 --> 00:14:21,870
to save your sworn enemy's
flesh and blood.

266
00:14:22,000 --> 00:14:23,270
How touching.

267
00:14:30,670 --> 00:14:31,680
Yes, Police Chief.

268
00:14:32,380 --> 00:14:34,310
This is Chae Hwa Young,
CEO of Dream Hotel.

269
00:14:35,080 --> 00:14:37,310
I was flustered and made a mistake.

270
00:14:37,920 --> 00:14:40,150
Since she had argued
with her grandfather before,

271
00:14:40,420 --> 00:14:42,990
I let my emotions get the best of me
and jumped to conclusions.

272
00:14:43,790 --> 00:14:44,790
Right.

273
00:14:46,220 --> 00:14:50,360
If this is pushed too hard,
it'll put you in an awkward position too.

274
00:14:51,130 --> 00:14:53,630
Please resolve this quickly
before the reporters find out.

275
00:14:54,230 --> 00:14:55,230
Thanks.

276
00:14:55,230 --> 00:14:57,130
And we should have a meal sometime.

277
00:14:57,640 --> 00:14:58,640
Thanks.

278
00:15:01,110 --> 00:15:03,640
(Suk Hee's Side Dishes)

279
00:15:09,550 --> 00:15:10,550
Mom.

280
00:15:11,520 --> 00:15:14,320
You went through so much, my dear Jang Mi.

281
00:15:14,820 --> 00:15:16,190
You were so worried about me, weren't you?

282
00:15:17,620 --> 00:15:20,220
I love it. The smell of my mom.

283
00:15:20,690 --> 00:15:23,890
My daughter. Are you hurt anywhere?

284
00:15:24,700 --> 00:15:27,030
You know your daughter's tough.

285
00:15:29,870 --> 00:15:33,270
- You're here, Tae Sook.
- I came from Vietnam when I heard.

286
00:15:33,540 --> 00:15:34,670
Are you copying me?

287
00:15:34,940 --> 00:15:37,110
Why do you have to worry
the family like this?

288
00:15:38,080 --> 00:15:40,310
Auntie, did you have a good trip?

289
00:15:40,740 --> 00:15:42,210
- What?
- Hey, Bo Ra, I told you...

290
00:15:42,210 --> 00:15:43,910
she was on a business trip, right?

291
00:15:43,950 --> 00:15:46,950
But where's your suitcase?

292
00:15:47,520 --> 00:15:49,220
Didn't you take a plane?

293
00:15:49,290 --> 00:15:52,320
I had to go somewhere for a bit.

294
00:15:52,920 --> 00:15:55,460
Bo Ra, didn't you miss your auntie?

295
00:15:55,560 --> 00:15:58,060
I was worried when you weren't here.

296
00:15:58,500 --> 00:16:01,100
Don't ever go on
a stupid business trip again.

297
00:16:02,230 --> 00:16:03,230
Come here.

298
00:16:05,370 --> 00:16:08,540
Is that so?
Bo Ra, you were worried about me.

299
00:16:09,210 --> 00:16:13,680
I'm not going anywhere again.
I'm going to stay right by your side.

300
00:16:13,880 --> 00:16:14,880
Okay?

301
00:16:18,420 --> 00:16:20,850
What? Oh Jang Mi was released?

302
00:16:21,150 --> 00:16:23,290
If not, I would've been
the one going to jail.

303
00:16:24,120 --> 00:16:27,120
Kang Baek Ho.
He's not the pushover he seems to be.

304
00:16:27,760 --> 00:16:30,760
Anyway, as long as Chairman Ma
doesn't wake up, time is on our side.

305
00:16:31,230 --> 00:16:33,630
How is Chairman Ma? Any improvement?

306
00:16:33,760 --> 00:16:35,770
I haven't been able to get any news
from his side.

307
00:16:36,230 --> 00:16:38,000
They have guards posted
all over the hospital.

308
00:16:38,300 --> 00:16:39,340
What's more,

309
00:16:39,640 --> 00:16:41,440
they filed for a restraining order.

310
00:16:41,440 --> 00:16:42,710
A restraining order?

311
00:16:44,010 --> 00:16:46,910
If Chairman Ma wakes up
and starts talking, we're in big trouble.

312
00:16:47,910 --> 00:16:51,880
Baek Ho, do you have proof
that all this was Chae Hwa Young's doing?

313
00:16:52,520 --> 00:16:54,420
Let's report it to the police right now.

314
00:16:54,490 --> 00:16:57,120
Exactly.
How could she knock down my grandfather...

315
00:16:57,190 --> 00:16:59,160
and then frame me for it?

316
00:16:59,160 --> 00:17:00,720
I'd like to do that.

317
00:17:01,160 --> 00:17:02,560
But it won't be easy.

318
00:17:03,830 --> 00:17:07,060
I submitted evidence to the police
proving you were innocent, Jang Mi,

319
00:17:07,130 --> 00:17:08,130
but it didn't work.

320
00:17:08,200 --> 00:17:10,730
So Chae Hwa Young had a mole
inside the police force.

321
00:17:10,970 --> 00:17:13,670
That's right.
And it's probably the same now.

322
00:17:14,300 --> 00:17:16,910
Even if we present evidence
that she's the culprit,

323
00:17:16,910 --> 00:17:18,210
I'm sure she'll get away with it.

324
00:17:18,280 --> 00:17:21,880
Since she's been lobbying people
in high places with all that money,

325
00:17:21,880 --> 00:17:23,110
I suppose that's possible.

326
00:17:23,180 --> 00:17:26,550
Then how long are we going to let
that wretched woman get away with this?

327
00:17:27,050 --> 00:17:28,820
She even knocked my father down.

328
00:17:28,820 --> 00:17:30,690
We have to cut off her money supply.

329
00:17:31,290 --> 00:17:34,490
Let's make her so broke
that she can't bribe anyone anymore.

330
00:17:34,930 --> 00:17:38,500
And then, when there's no one
left to back her up,

331
00:17:38,860 --> 00:17:41,530
- we'll make her pay for all her crimes.
- That's a good idea.

332
00:17:41,970 --> 00:17:44,470
First, we need to identify
Chae Hwa Young's moles...

333
00:17:44,770 --> 00:17:48,340
and her backers in the Prosecutor's Office
and political circles.

334
00:17:48,840 --> 00:17:50,340
We can start by cutting them off.

335
00:17:53,510 --> 00:17:55,480
(CEO Chae Hwa Young)

336
00:17:58,650 --> 00:17:59,680
Chae Hwa Young.

337
00:18:00,220 --> 00:18:03,850
Thanks to you, I almost had to live
as Oh Jang Mi instead of Ma Seo Rin.

338
00:18:04,150 --> 00:18:05,620
Too bad that plan fell through.

339
00:18:05,860 --> 00:18:08,530
Don't get cocky.
You won't last long here anyway.

340
00:18:09,960 --> 00:18:12,060
How long are you going to live such a lie?

341
00:18:12,260 --> 00:18:14,670
My mom has already filed a paternity suit.

342
00:18:14,970 --> 00:18:18,140
A DNA test is all it will take
to prove she's Grandfather's daughter.

343
00:18:18,440 --> 00:18:20,700
It's obvious where you're headed.

344
00:18:21,100 --> 00:18:22,510
I just came to let you know that.

345
00:18:29,310 --> 00:18:30,750
She's all talk.

346
00:18:31,780 --> 00:18:34,850
What can you do right now
besides run your mouth, Oh Jang Mi?

347
00:18:37,590 --> 00:18:39,060
The general shareholders' meeting
is coming up.

348
00:18:39,960 --> 00:18:42,890
Can I really take the throne?

349
00:18:43,990 --> 00:18:45,030
Kang Baek Ho.

350
00:18:45,730 --> 00:18:48,130
Of all people,
why are you the majority shareholder?

351
00:18:49,100 --> 00:18:50,430
Now that it's come to this,

352
00:18:51,240 --> 00:18:53,300
I have no choice but to win over
the board members.

353
00:19:08,250 --> 00:19:11,420
Jun Ho, the day of the final battle
is almost here.

354
00:19:11,690 --> 00:19:13,390
Once we get through this
general shareholders' meeting,

355
00:19:13,820 --> 00:19:15,790
Dream will officially be mine.

356
00:19:16,360 --> 00:19:18,530
Isn't this enough money for lobbying?

357
00:19:18,660 --> 00:19:20,460
What do you mean, "enough"?

358
00:19:21,500 --> 00:19:24,700
Do you think it's easy to change the minds
of those old geezer shareholders?

359
00:19:24,870 --> 00:19:28,340
To cover the 30 million dollars
that Jung Suk Hee stole disguised as Ali,

360
00:19:28,440 --> 00:19:29,810
we need more cash.

361
00:19:30,170 --> 00:19:33,540
I need to pay off the higher-ups
and silence the opposition.

362
00:19:33,980 --> 00:19:34,980
This time,

363
00:19:35,480 --> 00:19:37,810
I have to seal the deal for good.

364
00:19:39,320 --> 00:19:41,550
So you're saying you're going to
give them these bonsai trees?

365
00:19:42,590 --> 00:19:45,620
Yes. This Japanese White Pine
and this Chinese Juniper.

366
00:19:45,890 --> 00:19:47,360
If we just sell these two,

367
00:19:47,760 --> 00:19:49,630
we'll get one million dollars
in cash right away.

368
00:19:49,960 --> 00:19:51,930
I've already spoken to a big-time buyer.

369
00:19:52,460 --> 00:19:56,270
I'm sending someone over tonight,
so load the trees up quietly with them.

370
00:19:57,470 --> 00:19:58,470
Yes.

371
00:19:58,970 --> 00:20:00,740
I'll take care of it tonight.

372
00:20:01,140 --> 00:20:02,670
We don't have time.

373
00:20:03,310 --> 00:20:05,180
Before they make a move,

374
00:20:05,880 --> 00:20:07,310
we have to act first.

375
00:20:11,050 --> 00:20:13,380
CEO Chae will be going all out to prepare
for the general shareholders' meetings...

376
00:20:13,380 --> 00:20:15,250
and to win over the board members.

377
00:20:15,550 --> 00:20:17,450
She'll need a huge amount of money
for lobbying.

378
00:20:17,820 --> 00:20:19,790
Her Swiss bank account
won't be nearly enough.

379
00:20:19,860 --> 00:20:22,460
This week will probably be crunch time
for her preparations.

380
00:20:23,260 --> 00:20:27,000
And if her slush fund warehouse
is inside our hotel,

381
00:20:27,600 --> 00:20:29,630
Kang Jun Ho will be the one to act,
won't he?

382
00:20:29,900 --> 00:20:33,740
That's possible.
Lee Kang Hyuk is too exposed to us,

383
00:20:33,940 --> 00:20:36,470
so Chae Hwa Young will use
Kang Jun Ho now.

384
00:20:45,950 --> 00:20:47,750
(Authorized Personnel Only)

385
00:20:49,490 --> 00:20:51,150
(Restricted Area)

386
00:21:00,660 --> 00:21:01,970
But there's only
a landscaping warehouse...

387
00:21:02,030 --> 00:21:03,770
and a machine room
in the basement of the hotel annex.

388
00:21:04,130 --> 00:21:06,570
- Where could he be going?
- We'll find out soon enough.

389
00:21:46,580 --> 00:21:47,980
No CCTV here.

390
00:21:48,450 --> 00:21:50,010
(Restricted Area,
Authorized Personnel Only)

391
00:21:52,680 --> 00:21:54,850
It's 0843, and the star key.

392
00:21:54,920 --> 00:21:57,050
(Restricted Area,
Authorized Personnel Only)

393
00:22:51,370 --> 00:22:54,440
Hey. There's no room
for even the smallest mistake here.

394
00:22:55,450 --> 00:22:57,110
Do you have any idea
how much each of these bonsai costs?

395
00:22:57,380 --> 00:22:59,620
I'm sorry. I'll be more careful.

396
00:23:09,430 --> 00:23:10,460
Unbelievable...

397
00:23:10,790 --> 00:23:13,630
So Chae Hwa Young's slush fund
isn't paintings or cash,

398
00:23:14,230 --> 00:23:16,430
but things like bonsai and rare stones?

399
00:23:16,830 --> 00:23:19,300
The sheer scale of this is unbelievable.

400
00:23:20,000 --> 00:23:21,670
Paintings leave a paper trail,

401
00:23:21,670 --> 00:23:23,010
and there are always controversies
about forgeries,

402
00:23:23,170 --> 00:23:25,280
but bonsai trees are living antiques.

403
00:23:25,280 --> 00:23:27,680
Their value skyrockets over time,

404
00:23:28,040 --> 00:23:29,910
and they're traded in cash
only among insiders,

405
00:23:29,910 --> 00:23:31,180
so they're impossible to trace.

406
00:23:31,250 --> 00:23:32,650
But how are we supposed to move all this?

407
00:23:32,720 --> 00:23:34,450
We have to take everything
to finish her off for good.

408
00:23:34,890 --> 00:23:36,150
If we leave anything behind,

409
00:23:36,150 --> 00:23:38,290
Chae Hwa Young will come back
like a zombie.

410
00:23:38,560 --> 00:23:41,160
We have to leave her completely broke
so she can never make a comeback.

411
00:23:41,290 --> 00:23:44,360
I think I can get the password,

412
00:23:44,590 --> 00:23:46,000
but how do we get past the key lock?

413
00:23:46,330 --> 00:23:48,700
Leave that to me.

414
00:23:49,800 --> 00:23:52,570
I think I can open the lock.

415
00:23:59,380 --> 00:24:01,710
Congratulations on becoming
the interim Chairman, ma'am.

416
00:24:02,280 --> 00:24:03,610
Congratulations.

417
00:24:03,610 --> 00:24:05,850
Now at the general shareholders' meeting,

418
00:24:05,980 --> 00:24:07,920
you need to be confirmed as the Chairman.

419
00:24:09,420 --> 00:24:12,620
For that to happen,
I absolutely need your cooperation.

420
00:24:16,790 --> 00:24:19,460
I've put a Japanese White Pine
and a Chinese Juniper...

421
00:24:19,730 --> 00:24:20,800
in each of your cars.

422
00:24:22,530 --> 00:24:23,530
You do know...

423
00:24:23,870 --> 00:24:26,800
each of them
costs at least one million dollars, right?

424
00:24:27,900 --> 00:24:29,270
Of course.

425
00:24:29,710 --> 00:24:30,770
Thank you.

426
00:24:31,140 --> 00:24:33,210
Then I'll take it we're in the same boat.

427
00:24:33,610 --> 00:24:38,110
On that note,
let me show you my golden safe.

428
00:24:38,580 --> 00:24:40,550
So please give me your full support
at the general shareholders' meeting.

429
00:24:49,430 --> 00:24:50,760
Jang Mi.

430
00:24:50,760 --> 00:24:52,300
It looks like Chae Hwa Young...

431
00:24:52,400 --> 00:24:55,770
is trying to lock in Director Jo
and Director Yoon as allies...

432
00:24:55,830 --> 00:24:58,070
by taking them to her bonsai vault.

433
00:24:58,070 --> 00:24:59,670
That's faster than I thought.

434
00:25:11,720 --> 00:25:15,520
(Restricted Area,
Authorized Personnel Only)

435
00:25:16,920 --> 00:25:21,520
As you'll see from my safe,
I have plenty of ammunition.

436
00:25:21,960 --> 00:25:23,330
So don't worry about a thing.

437
00:25:23,660 --> 00:25:25,830
Just focus your efforts
on getting me the votes.

438
00:25:26,100 --> 00:25:29,000
I'm thrilled at the prospect
of seeing the golden safe.

439
00:25:29,570 --> 00:25:32,840
I can't wait to see how magnificent it is.

440
00:25:32,970 --> 00:25:36,570
I'm a little worried about the investors
who plan to vote against me...

441
00:25:36,570 --> 00:25:37,640
at the general shareholders' meeting.

442
00:25:37,910 --> 00:25:41,340
Frankly, Choi Ha Joon's side
has a significant stake.

443
00:25:41,880 --> 00:25:44,580
I'm truly counting on just the two of you.

444
00:25:44,880 --> 00:25:46,280
If you back me up,

445
00:25:46,520 --> 00:25:50,520
my safe is as good as yours.

446
00:25:50,750 --> 00:25:52,260
How could there be any doubt?

447
00:25:52,390 --> 00:25:55,830
We'll give you our full support.
Don't worry, CEO Chae.

448
00:25:55,930 --> 00:25:57,330
I mean, Chairman.

449
00:26:00,530 --> 00:26:02,270
We haven't even had
the general shareholders' meeting yet,

450
00:26:02,570 --> 00:26:04,430
and you're already calling me Chairman.

451
00:26:04,700 --> 00:26:07,000
People will say I'm counting my chickens
before they hatch.

452
00:26:08,970 --> 00:26:13,040
Now, when this door opens,
you will find that siding with me...

453
00:26:13,410 --> 00:26:15,910
was the best decision you ever made.

454
00:26:17,280 --> 00:26:18,320
Director Kang.

455
00:26:18,750 --> 00:26:19,750
Yes.

456
00:26:31,290 --> 00:26:32,300
Let's go.

457
00:26:35,230 --> 00:26:36,330
Come in.

458
00:26:36,430 --> 00:26:37,570
Look.

459
00:26:37,570 --> 00:26:38,770
My safe...

460
00:27:00,560 --> 00:27:02,730
What is this? CEO Chae.

461
00:27:03,230 --> 00:27:04,290
Are you kidding us?

462
00:27:04,930 --> 00:27:07,100
This is ridiculous. Let's go.

463
00:27:07,700 --> 00:27:08,700
Sir...

464
00:27:11,430 --> 00:27:12,570
This can't be happening.

465
00:27:13,170 --> 00:27:15,470
My trees and stones...

466
00:27:15,470 --> 00:27:16,570
Where did they go?

467
00:27:16,870 --> 00:27:17,970
My money...

468
00:27:17,970 --> 00:27:19,580
Where did all my money go?

469
00:27:19,910 --> 00:27:22,580
Where did it go? This can't be happening.

470
00:27:24,710 --> 00:27:26,520
Where did it go?

471
00:27:26,520 --> 00:27:28,790
Where did it go?

472
00:27:29,920 --> 00:27:31,860
- Chae Hwa Young.
- Where did it go? Where is it?

473
00:27:32,290 --> 00:27:34,090
Your kingdom ends here.

474
00:27:34,990 --> 00:27:36,160
You're finished.

475
00:28:03,290 --> 00:28:04,720
(The First Man)

476
00:28:04,790 --> 00:28:06,990
An anonymous benefactor...

477
00:28:06,990 --> 00:28:08,530
has donated the bonsai trees
to the Hope Orphanage...

478
00:28:08,590 --> 00:28:11,430
I bet Chae Hwa Young
is crying her eyes out right now.

479
00:28:12,130 --> 00:28:13,560
If you don't tell me everything,

480
00:28:13,560 --> 00:28:15,870
I'll report you
as Chae Hwa Young's accomplice.

481
00:28:16,100 --> 00:28:18,800
I have some insurance
against Chae Hwa Young,

482
00:28:19,000 --> 00:28:20,700
and I'll use it if it comes to that.

483
00:28:20,740 --> 00:28:23,670
There's someone who desperately wants
to see you, Mom.

484
00:28:23,840 --> 00:28:26,380
Are you by any chance
the person waiting for me?

485
00:28:26,510 --> 00:28:29,180
They must have met by now, right?

486
00:28:31,080 --> 00:28:33,080
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
